05:53.000 --> 06:02.000
At the stage of the implementation of the strategy, we can talk about the presence of rather typical difficulties,

06:02.000 --> 06:09.000
which many companies have in different industries with different strategies.

06:09.000 --> 06:16.000
The first difficulty is that not all employees of a company of a high level in the hierarchy,

06:16.000 --> 06:23.000
being up at 3 a.m., can clearly formulate the strategy of the company they work for.

06:23.000 --> 06:25.000
Not all of them.

06:25.000 --> 06:32.000
Employees of the second and third levels of the hierarchy should understand where we are going

06:32.000 --> 06:36.000
and what will happen to the company in two, three, four years.

06:36.000 --> 06:44.000
The second difficulty is that employees of the party's general line can formulate it.

06:44.000 --> 06:49.000
Maybe not at 3 a.m., being up, but they can formulate the party's general line.

06:49.000 --> 06:54.000
But they find it difficult to say what they should do at their workplace for this.

06:54.000 --> 07:01.000
And a very important point is what they should not do in order for the company to successfully implement its strategy.

07:02.000 --> 07:09.000
The second difficulty is how my interaction with the adjacent structural units should be.

07:09.000 --> 07:16.000
Employees should understand not only my role, but also the role of my colleagues from the structural units,

07:16.000 --> 07:22.000
how I interact with them in order for the party's general line to exist.

07:23.000 --> 07:32.000
The third difficulty is that employees can understand the party's general line and their own role,

07:32.000 --> 07:36.000
but they may disagree with the party's general line.

07:36.000 --> 07:39.000
There are a lot of reasons for this.

07:39.000 --> 07:45.000
One of the reasons is that they were not invited to the meeting where the strategy was being developed.

07:46.000 --> 07:52.000
Or the employees may have different views on how the company should develop.

07:52.000 --> 07:57.000
And since they disagree with the company's strategy,

07:57.000 --> 08:04.000
it is unlikely that they will invest 100% in order for this strategy to be implemented.

08:06.000 --> 08:10.000
The fourth difficulty is the lack of control.

08:11.000 --> 08:17.000
The strategy is translated into a package of actions that is clear for the employees.

08:17.000 --> 08:21.000
There are deadlines and indicators, but there is no control function.

08:21.000 --> 08:27.000
The company's management did not have time to set the control points and implement this control

08:27.000 --> 08:32.000
for the implementation of the measures that are necessary to achieve the strategic goals.

08:32.000 --> 08:38.000
Another difficulty is that the strategy of the company does not inspire people

08:38.000 --> 08:42.000
or is not related to their system of stimulation.

08:42.000 --> 08:50.000
The employees cannot say how the actions of the mentioned management are related to the system of compensation.

08:50.000 --> 08:57.000
They may simply not do it because there will be no rewards or punishments.

08:58.000 --> 09:02.000
Therefore, it is very important to introduce a strategy with a motivation system

09:02.000 --> 09:05.000
and a stimulus system for the employees.

09:05.000 --> 09:07.000
The conclusion is simple.

09:07.000 --> 09:14.000
The organization and its structural divisions need a simple and clear system of goals and indicators

09:14.000 --> 09:19.000
related to the system of accountability and the system of stimulation of the employees.

09:19.000 --> 09:25.000
And we will talk about how to create this system of goals and indicators for the company.

09:27.000 --> 09:32.000
The goal management logic is quite simple.

09:32.000 --> 09:37.000
As a rule, the goals of the business as a whole are created at the first stage.

09:37.000 --> 09:43.000
We consider the company as a single whole and we can say that the company has certain goals.

09:43.000 --> 09:47.000
After that, the declaration of the goals is carried out.

09:47.000 --> 09:51.000
The company is not limited to the goals of the business.

09:51.000 --> 09:55.000
We can say that the company has certain goals.

09:55.000 --> 10:02.000
After that, the decomposition is carried out and we talk about the goals of the company's structural divisions.

10:02.000 --> 10:05.000
About business units or functional divisions.

10:05.000 --> 10:11.000
At the stage number three, we develop the activities, actions, projects,

10:11.000 --> 10:16.000
the implementation of which is necessary to achieve the goals of the structural divisions.

10:16.000 --> 10:21.000
After developing this package of activities, we can start to implement them.

10:21.000 --> 10:23.000
Here is a very important point.

10:23.000 --> 10:26.000
The function of management control is needed.

10:26.000 --> 10:33.000
And, as a rule, not everything goes as we planned, not everything goes as we planned.

10:33.000 --> 10:38.000
Therefore, very often companies have to make adjustments to the package of actions

10:38.000 --> 10:41.000
