12:05.000 --> 12:11.000
At the first stage, the company sets its own financial goals.

12:11.000 --> 12:19.000
We can say that most companies exist to make a profit.

12:19.000 --> 12:24.000
And we talk about the targeted profits that we want to make

12:24.000 --> 12:30.000
in the framework of the project number one, the project finance.

12:30.000 --> 12:36.000
After we have determined our own financial goals at the first stage,

12:36.000 --> 12:42.000
we think about what positions on the market we want to achieve

12:42.000 --> 12:46.000
in order to make the targeted profit that we want to make.

12:46.000 --> 12:50.000
At the second stage, we think about who our client is,

12:50.000 --> 12:54.000
who could provide us with these profits,

12:54.000 --> 12:57.000
and what our product portfolio should look like

12:57.000 --> 13:01.000
in order to make the targeted group that we have chosen

13:01.000 --> 13:05.000
count the money that we want to make.

13:05.000 --> 13:11.000
So, the goals at the second stage are the goals in the client-product projection.

13:11.000 --> 13:17.000
The question that we have to answer here is very simple and complex.

13:17.000 --> 13:21.000
The question is, who and what do we sell to?

13:21.000 --> 13:26.000
What are the leading positions in the targeted segments that we want to achieve?

13:26.000 --> 13:30.000
And how should our product portfolio look like

13:30.000 --> 13:35.000
in order to achieve the goals in the top projection, the finance projection?

13:35.000 --> 13:38.000
Having determined the goals at the second projection,

13:38.000 --> 13:42.000
we move on to the third, which is usually called the business process.

13:42.000 --> 13:49.000
Here we list the goals that we should achieve in the chain of our own processes,

13:49.000 --> 13:52.000
starting with the design of the product,

13:52.000 --> 13:56.000
continuing with the purchase of resources, production, branding,

13:56.000 --> 13:59.000
sales, distribution and services.

13:59.000 --> 14:05.000
In the third projection, we think about the business processes

14:05.000 --> 14:08.000
that our business consists of.

14:08.000 --> 14:14.000
The fourth stage is the goals in the personnel projection.

14:14.000 --> 14:19.000
We think about the goals that we should achieve

14:19.000 --> 14:24.000
in terms of the competence of our personnel,

14:24.000 --> 14:28.000
in terms of their satisfaction and motivation

14:28.000 --> 14:35.000
in order to achieve the goals in the client-process projection and finance.

14:35.000 --> 14:39.000
So, the logic of the goal setting is quite simple.

14:39.000 --> 14:44.000
The first stage is finance, the second stage is the client and product portfolio,

14:44.000 --> 14:48.000
the third stage is the business processes,

14:48.000 --> 14:51.000
