The general logic of this work is presented on this slide.

01:28:56.000 --> 01:29:00.000
There is a corporate card,

01:29:00.000 --> 01:29:04.000
and we are trying to make cards for the main structural divisions.

01:29:04.000 --> 01:29:08.000
Everything here depends on the organizational structure of the company.

01:29:08.000 --> 01:29:12.000
If the company consists of relatively large companies,

01:29:12.000 --> 01:29:16.000
then the company is a company that has a large number of employees.

01:29:16.000 --> 01:29:20.000
If the company consists of a small company,

01:29:20.000 --> 01:29:24.000
then the business units are relatively independent.

01:29:24.000 --> 01:29:28.000
Each of them has its own clients.

01:29:28.000 --> 01:29:32.000
For clients, a product portfolio is made.

01:29:32.000 --> 01:29:38.000
The business units cards will be the same as the business price cards.

01:29:38.000 --> 01:29:44.000
There will be finances, income minus expenses equals profits.

01:29:44.000 --> 01:29:48.000
There will be external clients that need to be serviced,

01:29:48.000 --> 01:29:52.000
with whom you need to build relations, loyalty to which needs to be increased.

01:29:52.000 --> 01:29:56.000
There will be processes, there will be some kind of personnel policy,

01:29:56.000 --> 01:30:00.000
and goals in the area of infrastructure.

01:30:00.000 --> 01:30:04.000
But the company usually has a number of service units,

01:30:04.000 --> 01:30:08.000
accounting, IT department, personnel management department,

01:30:08.000 --> 01:30:12.000
legal department.

01:30:12.000 --> 01:30:16.000
For them, too, cards are needed.

01:30:16.000 --> 01:30:20.000
And they also have their own projection of finances.

01:30:20.000 --> 01:30:24.000
All these structural units must fit into the budget.

01:30:24.000 --> 01:30:30.000
If the company lives in the budget, then the accounting, IT, HR,

01:30:30.000 --> 01:30:34.000
personnel management, and legal department have their own budgets.

01:30:34.000 --> 01:30:38.000
They have their own budgets, which they protected at the meeting of the Budget Committee,

01:30:38.000 --> 01:30:42.000
signed with blood and must fulfill.

01:30:42.000 --> 01:30:44.000
Therefore, they also have a projection of finances.

01:30:44.000 --> 01:30:48.000
They all have a projection of processes.

01:30:48.000 --> 01:30:50.000
In accounting, their processes are carried out,

01:30:50.000 --> 01:30:52.000
in IT department, their processes,

01:30:52.000 --> 01:30:54.000
in legal department, their processes.

01:30:54.000 --> 01:30:56.000
Everyone also has a projection of personnel.

01:30:56.000 --> 01:31:00.000
People work everywhere, people have some competencies,

01:31:00.000 --> 01:31:02.000
people have some kind of satisfaction or dissatisfaction.

01:31:02.000 --> 01:31:06.000
All this needs to be measured, it needs to be managed.

01:31:06.000 --> 01:31:08.000
There is also infrastructure in each department.

01:31:08.000 --> 01:31:14.000
The question is whether there is a projection of the client.

01:31:14.000 --> 01:31:20.000
In many companies, the concept of an internal client is introduced.

01:31:20.000 --> 01:31:26.000
And I want to tell you about this using the example of a company that works on the market of buildings

01:31:26.000 --> 01:31:30.000
made of quickly assembled metal structures.

01:31:30.000 --> 01:31:34.000
The organization consists of six main structural units.

01:31:34.000 --> 01:31:40.000
Construction, logistics, construction of finances,

01:31:40.000 --> 01:31:42.000
and development of the market.

01:31:42.000 --> 01:31:48.000
If you look at the map of the goals and indicators of the logistics department in this company,

01:31:48.000 --> 01:31:56.000
it says that the internal client is to increase the satisfaction of internal clients.

01:31:56.000 --> 01:32:00.000
Who is the internal client of the logistics department?

01:32:00.000 --> 01:32:04.000
It is a colleague from the structural units.

01:32:04.000 --> 01:32:08.000
He works with the construction department more than with the sales department.

01:32:08.000 --> 01:32:12.000
They meet more often, argue more often, cooperate more often.

01:32:12.000 --> 01:32:18.000
But in any case, the logistics department in this company communicates with everyone,

01:32:18.000 --> 01:32:24.000
interacts with everyone, argues with everyone, sometimes there is a conflict with someone.

01:32:24.000 --> 01:32:30.000
And the management of the company believes that it is necessary to use an indicator called

01:32:30.000 --> 01:32:34.000
the satisfaction index of the internal client,

01:32:34.000 --> 01:32:40.000
which would stimulate the logistics department to increase the satisfaction of the colleagues

01:32:40.000 --> 01:32:44.000
with whom they have to work.

01:32:44.000 --> 01:32:50.000
Once a quarter, the logistics department receives points from the sales department,

01:32:50.000 --> 01:32:56.000
from the construction department, from the financial department,

01:32:56.000 --> 01:33:00.000
and from the organizational development department.

01:33:00.000 --> 01:33:06.000
These are colleagues at the same level in the hierarchy, plus a point from the general director.

01:33:06.000 --> 01:33:12.000
The points are evaluated by three parameters.

01:33:12.000 --> 01:33:16.000
The first parameter is the quality of the performance of the duties.

01:33:16.000 --> 01:33:28.000
The financial director is asked how satisfied he is with the quality of the performance of the duties of the main logistics department.

01:33:28.000 --> 01:33:34.000
How satisfied he is with the quality of the work of the logistics department.

01:33:34.000 --> 01:33:40.000
And how satisfied he is with the time of performance of the duties.

01:33:40.000 --> 01:33:48.000
The second parameter is how satisfied you are with the politeness and friendliness of the logistics department.

01:33:48.000 --> 01:33:50.000
So, the three main parameters.

01:33:50.000 --> 01:33:54.000
The quality of the performance of the duties in relation to someone as an internal client.

01:33:54.000 --> 01:34:00.000
The second parameter is the time of performance of the duties in relation to someone as an internal client.

01:34:00.000 --> 01:34:04.000
And the third parameter is politeness and friendliness in the process of corporate communication.

01:34:04.000 --> 01:34:06.000
This is also evaluated by points.

01:34:06.000 --> 01:34:14.000
The management hopes that this system will allow the relationship in the team to heal a little.

01:34:14.000 --> 01:34:18.000
If I know that my colleagues from the structural departments will give me points at the end of the quarter,

01:34:18.000 --> 01:34:26.000
then I try not to use non-normative vocabulary and I am not satisfied with them at all.

01:34:26.000 --> 01:34:34.000
In fact, this is a circular assessment, because everyone gives a point to everyone and, in turn, gets points from everyone.

01:34:34.000 --> 01:34:44.000
In principle, this is anonymous, because the logistics department receives points and comments from the structural departments.

01:34:44.000 --> 01:34:50.000
The points are not signed and the comments are not signed either.

01:34:50.000 --> 01:34:56.000
But in principle, as a rule, the logistics department guesses who wrote what comment.

01:34:56.000 --> 01:35:04.000
But it is very important to write a comment, because the logistics department must understand why they were given such a low point,

01:35:04.000 --> 01:35:08.000
what they need to work on, or why they were given such a high point.

01:35:08.000 --> 01:35:13.000
In this company, this is related to the compensation system.

01:35:13.000 --> 01:35:17.000
The quarterly bonus is tied to this point.

01:35:18.000 --> 01:35:24.000
Bonuses start to be added from the average point equal to 7.

01:35:24.000 --> 01:35:32.000
That is, if less than 7 points were scored for quality, or for timeliness, or for politeness and friendliness, then there are no bonuses.

01:35:32.000 --> 01:35:40.000
Bonuses start to be added quarterly, if the average point is 7.1, 7.2 and so on.

01:35:40.000 --> 01:35:43.000
The more points, the more bonuses.

01:35:43.000 --> 01:35:49.000
The so-called satisfaction index of the internal client.

01:35:49.000 --> 01:36:02.000
The internal clients must be satisfied with the quality of their duties, their timeliness, and the third parameter, politeness and friendliness in the process of corporate communication.

